				\begin{document}$$ \% \,{\rm{activity}}= \% \,{{\rm{activity}}}_{{\rm{\max }}}/(1+[{\rm{triclosan}}]/{{\rm{IC}}}_{50}),$$\end{document}%activity=%activitymax/(1+[triclosan]/IC50),assuming competitive inhibition and using the Cheng-Prusoff equation36. Errors were calculated from multiple kinetic runs. The kinetics of PvDHFR carried a larger error than HsDHFR because PvDHFR was prone to loss of activity during purification and storage. Duplicates were performed and IC50 values were obtained by fitting the data shown in Fig. 1C to the above equation (MatLab software, Mathworks – curves were fitted by Fabrice Gielen, Cambridge).
